{
    "level": "B1",
    "intro": "In this topic you will learn the difference between <strong>another, other, the other</strong>, and also <strong>others / the others</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "ONE MORE",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "<strong>Another</strong> = one more or a different single thing.",
            "example": "Can I have another coffee?"
        },
        {
            "label": "DIFFERENT / MORE",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "<strong>Other</strong> is used with plural nouns or uncountable nouns.",
            "example": "other people / other information"
        },
        {
            "label": "THE REMAINING ONE",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "<strong>The other</strong> = the second one / the remaining one.",
            "example": "One bag is mine, and the other bag is yours."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Main contrasts",
    "intro": "See which form works with which type of noun.",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "one thing",
            "title": "another + singular noun",
            "subtitle": "another day, another cup, another idea"
        },
        {
            "label": "other / additional",
            "title": "other + plural / uncountable noun",
            "subtitle": "other books, other people, other information"
        },
        {
            "label": "the specific second one",
            "title": "the other + singular noun",
            "subtitle": "the other hand, the other room"
        },
        {
            "label": "without a noun",
            "title": "others / the others",
            "subtitle": "Some are ready; the others are late."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. When to use each form",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Another = one more",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "<strong>Another</strong> goes with a singular noun and often means “one more” or “a different one”.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Can I have another sandwich?",
                    "ua": "Can I have another sandwich?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Let us try another method.",
                    "ua": "Let us try another method."
                },
                {
                    "en": "She stayed for another hour.",
                    "ua": "She stayed for another hour."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Other = different / additional",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>Other</strong> stands before a plural noun or an uncountable noun.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Other students were already inside.",
                    "ua": "Other students were already inside."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Do you have any other questions?",
                    "ua": "Do you have any other questions?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "We need other information.",
                    "ua": "We need other information."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "The other / the others = the remaining one(s)",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "<strong>The other</strong> means the specific second or remaining one; <strong>the others</strong> means the rest of the group.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "I have two keys. One is old and the other is new.",
                    "ua": "I have two keys. One is old and the other is new."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Some students passed, but the others failed.",
                    "ua": "Some students passed, but the others failed."
                },
                {
                    "en": "This side is clean. The other side is dirty.",
                    "ua": "This side is clean. The other side is dirty."
                }
            ],
            "note": "Without a noun, use <strong>others / the others</strong>."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Common mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Mistake 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Using another with a plural noun.",
            "wrong": "another books",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">other books</span> / <span class=\"font-mono\">another book</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Using other without a noun when you need others.",
            "wrong": "Some students are here, and other are late.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">Some students are here, and others are late.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Leaving out the in a specific contrast.",
            "wrong": "One shoe is black, other shoe is brown.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">One shoe is black, the other shoe is brown.</span>"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Quick summary",
    "items": [
        "<strong>Another</strong> = one more / a different single thing.",
        "<strong>Other</strong> = other or additional people / things; used with plural or uncountable nouns.",
        "<strong>The other</strong> = the specific second or remaining one.",
        "<strong>Others / the others</strong> are used without a noun.",
        "Ask yourself: is it one more, other ones in general, or the specific remaining one?"
    ]
}

